content:
A service territory represents the geographic or functional area where your business operates.

Workforce Engagement is available in Enterprise, Performance, and Unlimited Editions. Shift Scheduling is available in the Contact Center Stock Keeping Unit (SKU), Einstein 1 Service Edition, and Service Suites.

When creating a workload history, forecast, or capacity plan in Workforce Engagement, you select a service territory. This service territory determines the time zone used to display the workload history and its related forecast and capacity plan.

Each shift that you create is based on a single service territory. The Match Territory scheduling rule type checks if a service resource belongs to a shift's service territory.

To create a service territory, open Service Territories in the App Launcher, click New, name your service territory, select operating hours, and make it active. Save your changes.

Service territory members are service resources who work in the associated territory within the specified hours. You can assign service resources to service territories on the resource detail page or territory detail page.

The primary territory is where the resource works most often. Secondary territories are territories where the resource can be assigned if needed. A resource can have more than one secondary territory but only one primary territory.
title: Creating Service Territories
